From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 16:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] crypto: rk3288 - inherit the fallback ahash statesize

The rk3288 driver implements import() and export() by proxying its
software fallback tfm, so the state it exports is the fallback's
state. The sha256/sha1/md5 shashes now use the partial block API and
export their partial block alongside the core state plus a trailing
length byte (e.g. SHA256_SHASH_STATE_SIZE is 105 bytes), so the
fallback's statesize exceeds the driver's declared
sizeof(struct sha256_state) (104) and export() overruns the caller's
buffer. The self-tests catch the overrun and reject all three hashes
at every boot:

  alg: ahash: rk-sha256 export() overran state buffer on test vector 0, cfg="import/export"
  alg: self-tests for sha256 using rk-sha256 failed (rc=-75)

(likewise rk-sha1 and rk-md5, observed on an ASUS Chromebook C201,
RK3288/veyron-speedy, kernel 7.1.3)

Inherit the fallback's statesize when the tfm is initialised, matching
what the driver already does for reqsize one statement above, and what
sun8i-ce -- the same fallback-proxy design -- already does.

Fixes: 3bf533787910 ("crypto: sha256 - Use the partial block API")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 drivers/crypto/rockchip/rk3288_crypto_ahash.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/crypto/rockchip/rk3288_crypto_ahash.c
+++ b/drivers/crypto/rockchip/rk3288_crypto_ahash.c
@@ -362,6 +362,9 @@
 				 sizeof(struct rk_ahash_rctx) +
 				 crypto_ahash_reqsize(tctx->fallback_tfm));
 
+	crypto_ahash_set_statesize(tfm,
+				   crypto_ahash_statesize(tctx->fallback_tfm));
+
 	return 0;
 }
 
